  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Asthma among low-income, minority children remains a prime example of health disparities that
      are resistant to change. Demonstrations of reductions in disproportionate hospitalizations in
      controlled trials are limited. We performed a controlled clinical trial of an Asthma Coach to
      reduce hospitalizations among low-income, African American children.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
